Requires

   POSIX environment
   Standard POSIX /bin/sh
   curl(1) client

To install (as root)

   # Install without the *.sh extension.
   # System wide programs do not have extensions.

   install --mode=755 ddns-updater.sh /usr/local/bin/ddns-updater
   install --mode=644 cron.d/ddns-updater /etc/cron.d/

   mkdir --parents ~/.config/ddns-updater

Note:

  The configuration files can be installed in:

      $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/	   or
      /etc/ddns-updater/

Configure for ducdns.org

   # Copy TOKEN from your account page
   # SUBDOMAIN.duckdns.org

   echo TOKEN > $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/duckdns.token
   echo SUBDOMAIN,SUBDOMAIN... > $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/duckdns.domains

Configure for dns.he.net

   echo PASSWORD > $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/henet.pass
   echo SUBDOMAIN,SUBDOMAIN... >  $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/henet.domains
